Chocolate Mocha Mousse
Judy Heumann

5 1-oz squares unsweetened chocolate
2 envelopes unflavored gelatin
3/4 cup sugar, divided into thirds
1/4 cup coffee or chocolate liqueur
1/2 cup very strong, very hot coffee
6 eggs, separated
2 cups whipping cream

Blend chocolate in a food processor or blender along with gelatin and 1/4 cup sugar until finely chopped.

Add hot coffee and blend until the chocolate melts and gelatin and sugar dissolve.

Add the liqueur, mix and set aside.

Beat egg yolks in a mixer or food processor until thick - about five minutes.  Gradually add 1/4 cup sugar and beat until dissolved.  Set aside.

Beat egg whites with mixer until stiff.  Add remaining 1/4 cup sugar and beat until stiff(er).

Whip cream with a mixer until stiff.

Combine egg yolk mixture with chocolate/gelatin/coffee mixture.  Then, mix that with egg whites and whip cream.  Fold together.

Turn into an 8-cup mold or bowl and chill for several hours or overnight.
